<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-8053] Memory leak when adding/removing a lot of routes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-8053</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Dynamically adding/removing routes to camel causes registrations in org.apache.camel.builder.ErrorHandlerBuilderRef.handlers (Map&amp;lt;RouteContext, ErrorHandlerBuilder&amp;gt;) for RouteContext instances. Those never get removed and can cause leaks if memory consuming objects are attached in the RouteContext for example constant definitions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12755595">CAMEL-8053</key>
            <summary>Memory leak when adding/removing a lot of routes</summary>
